 @{fg shine}Keyboard Shortcuts:@{fg text}


 The normal method for printing FunFont graphics to a channel is through
 Arexx parsing of keywords, however sometimes you need to be a little bit
 more responsive.

 Therefore the more frequently used graphics have been allocated certain
 keyboard shortcuts (for example pressing Alt-y prints a "Yes!" graphic).

 I have tried to make the shortcuts as easy as possible to remember, and
 have also included a reference sheet similar to the one for the @{fg fill}CODES@{fg text}.

 FunFont currently supports these keymaps...

 CDN (Canadian Franįais)
 CH1 (Suisse)
 CH2 (Schweiz)
 D   (Deutsch)
 DK  (Dansk)
 E   (Espaņol)
 F   (Franįais)
 GB  (British)
 I   (Italiana)
 N   (Norsk)
 S   (Svenskt)
 USA (American)


