@node "ansi" "FunFont enhanced ANSI"@prev "Shortcuts"@next "Send"


 @{fg shine}FunFont enhanced ANSI:@{fg text}


 FunFont makes it easy to create superb graphics to @{" Send " link "send"} to a channel or
 to swap with other FunFont users.

 By adding a selection of carefully designed "building block" graphics to
 the inventory of available ansi-type characters, you are no longer limited
 to creating graphics made out of the usual backslashes and underscores.


 Follow these easy steps to create your own @{fg fill}FANSI@{fg text} graphics...

 1: Click on the @{fg fill}FansiMaker@{fg text} icon (if installed).

 OR...

 1: Launch your Workbench Font preference program (Sys:Prefs/Fonts).

 2: Select @{fg fill}FunFont@{fg text} size @{fg fill}7,9 or 11@{fg text} as the Default font.

 3: Click on the @{fg fill}USE@{fg text} gadget.

 4: Start creating !!! (Ed which is located in your C: directory will do).


 TIP: @{bg fill}PUT A "ONE PIXEL SPACE" (Alt-t) AT THE LEFT HAND EDGE OF EVERY LINE.@{bg background}
      @{bg fill}THIS IS SO THAT Amirc DOES'NT CONFUSE "/" AS COMMAND IDENTIFIERS.   @{bg background}

 TIP: @{bg fill}YOU CAN INCORPORATE ANY OF THE GRAPHICS THAT ARE ACCESSIBLE FROM THE@{bg background}
      @{bg fill}KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS...BUT WATCH THAT SPACING AS THEY'RE NOT UNIFORMED@{bg background}

 TIP: @{bg fill}FOR WYSIWYG EDITING OF FANSI CHARACTERS AND FUNFONT GRAPHICS, USE   @{bg background}
      @{bg fill}THE FANSIMAKER UTILITY (COPIED TO YOUR SYSTEM DURING INSTALLATION)  @{bg background}


 @{" VIEW " link "fansi"} FANSI keystroke reference sheet.


 @{bg mark}Send your works of art to: @{fg shine}funfont@c-design.tcp.co.uk@{bg background}@{fg text}

@endnode

