 @{fg shine}Send (F)ANSI graphics to a channel:@{fg text}


 Once you have created your (F)ANSI graphics, you will need to be able
 to send them to a channel.

 @{fg shine}Tipop@concentric.net@{fg text} (The Possessed Programmer) has kindly provided the
 the necessary script to do this for you.

 The script is copied to your @{fg fill}AmIRC:Rexx/@{fg text} directory during the installation.


 USAGE: @{fg shine}/RX Send <file>@{fg text}  Where @{fg shine}<file>@{fg text} is full path to file.


 OR...

 You can use the @{fg fill}@{bg shine}þNEW@{fg text}@{bg background} SendReq command, which will prompt you to choose a 
 Fansi graphic from a requester... 


 USAGE: @{fg shine}/RX SendReq@{fg text}


 TIP: @{bg fill}DO NOT SEND TOO MANY GRAPHICS TO A CHANNEL AS THIS CAN CAUSE FLOODING.@{bg background}

 TIP: @{bg fill}KEEP GRAPHICS TO A FEW LINES BY USING THE EXTENDED FUNFONT CHARACTERS.@{bg background}

 TIP: @{bg fill}CHECK OUT THE EXAMPLES I MADE (BADLY) IN THE DIRECTORY    AMIRC:FANSI/@{gb background}

@endnode

