 @{fg shine}Figlet:@{fg text}


 Figlet is an Amiga port of a text rendering program written by @{fg shine}Steve Tibbet@{fg text}

 FunFont will by default improve the look of all Figlets, however it is
 possible to use the extended @{fg fill}FANSI@{fg text} characters to create and render FunFont
 enhanced Figlets.


 I have included a couple of example Figlet fonts for you to play with...


 @{" FunFont01.flf " link "images/fig1.pic/main"} is a plain, vertical font.

 @{" FunFont02.flf " link "images/fig2.pic/main"} is a slanted, raised block font.


 Both examples are copied to @{fg fill}AmIRC:Figlet/@{fg text} during installation.



 USAGE: @{fg shine}/FIGLET -f <fontname> <text>@{fg text}



 Figlet is NOT included in the FunFont package.

 Figlet can be obtained from @{fg fill}AMINET:text/show/figlet.lha@{fg text}

@endnode

